      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show reminder URLs in Reminders notes",
        "body": "Closes #59.\n\nKeeps writing the EventKit URL property and mirrors a tool-owned `remindctl URL: ...` line into notes so the link is visible in Reminders.app without treating authored `URL: ...` notes as generated content. Editing a URL replaces the managed line; clearing a URL removes only the managed line and leaves authored notes intact. Notes-only add/edit paths now preserve authored notes exactly when no URL mirror is involved.\n\nValidated with `make check`. Live EventKit proof on macOS 27.0 (26A5368g) with Reminders full access: adding a reminder with `--url https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof` returned notes containing `remindctl URL: https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof`, editing to `https://example.com/openclaw-remindctl-proof-v2` replaced that managed line, and `--clear-url` removed the URL field while leaving the authored notes as `Codex proof notes`; the disposable proof reminder was deleted afterward. Added regression coverage showing authored `URL: https://example.com/old` lines survive URL replace/clear and notes-only text, including spacing and empty strings, is preserved without a URL mirror.\n",
        "branch": "fix-reminder-url-field",
